President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation for Father's Day, expressing gratitude for the important role that fathers play in our lives. The proclamation recognizes the sacrifices that fathers make and the values they instill in their children. The President also emphasizes the need for responsible fatherhood and encourages fathers to be mentors for young people in need of guidance. The proclamation highlights the importance of being present in the lives of our children and expresses gratitude for the men who have enriched our lives. President Obama officially declares June 19, 2016, as Father's Day and calls upon all citizens to observe the day with appropriate programs and activities.